'''St Hugh's Preparatory School''' is a coeducational fee paying school in [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]], [[Jamaica]] for children aged 3 to 12.<ref name="WS"/> It is so highly regarded in Jamaica that it is advisable to put one's child on the waiting list ''before'' they are born.<ref>[http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080602/news/news5.html Parents go extra mile to register kids before birth], Sonia Mitchell & Avia Collinder, Jamaica Gleaner, 2008-06-02.</ref>

==History==
The school was founded in 1899 by [[Enos Nuttall|Archbishop Nuttall]] as part of the [[Deaconess Home School]], which later became [[St Hugh's High School]] for girls. The Preparatory department moved to its present location in September 1959.<ref name="HB3">{{Harvnb|Anon|2008|p=3}}.</ref> The school buildings were designed and constructed by [[Bill Hodges (architect)|Bill Hodges]], architect, sometime Chief Town Planner and the then school PTA President.<ref name="HB3"/>

==Inclusion of deaf students==
An integrated unit for deaf students was established during the mid 1960s, the first of its kind in Jamaica.<ref>[http://www.jamdeaf.org.jm/about-us/the-jad-over-sixty-years-of-service-to-the Brief History & Milestones], Jamaica Association for the Deaf, 2009.</ref>

==Insignia==
===Motto===
The school motto is the latin "Fidelitas" which can be translated either as "Faithful",<ref name="HB3"/> or as "Loyal and faithful to the end".<ref name="WS">[http://www.sthughspreparatory.com/About%20Our%20School.html School web site].</ref>

===Patron Saint===
[[Hugh of Lincoln|Saint Hugh]] (Hugh of Lincoln) was born at [[Avallon]], [[Burgundy (region)|Burgundy]], [[France]] c1140.<ref name="HB3"/> After becoming a priest he was invited by [[Henry II of England]] to work in [[England]] and in 1186 was elected [[Bishop]] of [[Lincoln, Lincolnshire|Lincoln]].<ref name="HB3"/> He was noted for his kindness to both people and animals and kept a pet swan. Swans are generally very fierce but this one had a special relationship with him.<ref name="HB3"/>

===Emblem===
The School<U+2019>s emblem is a white swan on a blue shield.<ref name="HB1">{{Harvnb|Anon|2008|p=1}}.</ref>

===Uniform===
Yellow [[oxford shirt]], navy blue shorts/trousers/skirt/[[skort]], navy blue socks, black shoes and belts, blue or black hair accessories, no jewellery.<ref name="HB9&10">{{Harvnb|Anon|2008|pp=9-10}}.</ref>

